This paper focuses on developing a neural data-driven summarizer for scientific publications, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with information retrieval (IR) and graph-based modeling, which are relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses deep learning (DL) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DL (Machine Learning).
